cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with face alignment, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of convolutional neural networks and 3D morphable models suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that the paper may be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the challenges of labeling landmarks, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of 3D information and the synthesis of face images suggest that the paper may also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with aligning faces in different poses, which suggests that it may be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
